cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.CR, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper primarily focuses on network softwarization and network function virtualization (NFV), which are related to networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The proposed model for dynamic reliability-aware service placement is formulated as an infinite horizon Markov decision process (MDP), which is related to systems and control. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The deployment of software functions on commodity servers instead of traditional hardware-based middle-boxes is related to distributed computing. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper mentions meeting the service level agreement, which is related to security and cryptography. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a sub-optimal method based on the Viterbi algorithm and an algorithm named VRSSP-based Value Iteration, which are related to artificial intelligence.
